From: Easwar Hariharan <eahariha@linux.microsoft.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jul 2024 05:27:32 +0000
Subject: sfc: falcon: Make I2C terminology more inclusive
Patch-mainline: v6.11-rc1
Git-commit: ba88b47816a2089cd270a38fc002bc7df13f8ebe
References: jsc#PED-11367

I2C v7, SMBus 3.2, and I3C 1.1.1 specifications have replaced "master/slave"
with more appropriate terms. Inspired by Wolfram's series to fix drivers/i2c/,
fix the terminology for users of I2C_ALGOBIT bitbanging interface, now that
the approved verbiage exists in the specification.

Reviewed-by: Martin Habets <habetsm.xilinx@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Simon Horman <horms@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Easwar Hariharan <eahariha@linux.microsoft.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20240711052734.1273652-5-eahariha@linux.microsoft.com
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/sfc/falcon/falcon.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/sfc/falcon/falcon.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/sfc/falcon/falcon.c
@@ -367,7 +367,7 @@ static const struct i2c_algo_bit_data fa
 	.getsda		= falcon_getsda,
 	.getscl		= falcon_getscl,
 	.udelay		= 5,
-	/* Wait up to 50 ms for slave to let us pull SCL high */
+	/* Wait up to 50 ms for target to let us pull SCL high */
 	.timeout	= DIV_ROUND_UP(HZ, 20),
 };
 
